  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nPresently, whenever a `Deposit`, `Exit`, `AttesterSlashing` or `ProposerSlashing` is given to the `BeaconChain` it does not verify it before adding it to the \"inclusion queue\".\r\n\r\nTherefore, if one submits an invalid object it will cause block production to fail indefinitely thereafter.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nNote: this code is currently in #264, do not start issue until it has been merged. Exits queues have not been implemented yet, they will come soon.\r\n\r\nAdd verification steps to the `BeaconChain::receive_x_for_inclusion` where `x = [deposit, attester_slashing, proposer_slashing, exit]` functions.\r\n",
